      <h1 class='title'>London Underground</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 17 December 2002 vol 396 cc48-50WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_48ws' title='Col. 48WS &mdash; HC Deb 17 December 2002 vol 396 c48WS' name='column_48ws' href='#column_48ws' rel='bookmark'>48WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0396P0_20021217_CWS_27'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-alistair-darling' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0396P0_20021217_CWS_27' title='Link to this speech by Mr Alistair Darling' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-alistair-darling" title="Mr Alistair Darling">The Secretary of State for Transport (Mr. Alistair Darling)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">This statement is in response to Early Day Motion 285 which expressed concerns about the contingent liability in respect of the London Underground PPP notified by my Minute of 4 December.</p><p>The contingent liability would crystallise only in the event that the Mayor of London proceeds with his legal challenge to the plans, and in the event that any successful challenge has a material adverse effect on an Infrastructure Company. Significant risk is transferred
          
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_49ws' title='Col. 49WS &mdash; HC Deb 17 December 2002 vol 396 c49WS' name='column_49ws' href='#column_49ws' rel='bookmark'>49WS</a>
          to the private sector under the London Underground PPP. Should the contingent liability materialise, the amounts payable will in large part be attributable to
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_50ws' title='Col. 50WS &mdash; HC Deb 17 December 2002 vol 396 c50WS' name='column_50ws' href='#column_50ws' rel='bookmark'>50WS</a>
          paying for the investment that has already been undertaken under the PPP contracts and has gone into the Tube.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
